description:
New version with a reprocess of the background and stars

------------
I am happy to post this new shot composed of 2 different setups, the RGB come from my fisrt newton 10'' from the summer 2018, and the luminance from my new setup with the 12''newton .
The 8th of October in the evening, I just started the night as usual with some SHO subs because of the moon , and it shows good FWHM, so I decided to modifiy completly my schedule and shoot this very nice galaxy, after the moonset !
I had only time to shoot new Luminance but it was worth it ....

From Lacerta Newton 300/1200

From Lacerta Newton 250/1000 from summer 2018
